ke, H. J., and Dirks, R. W. (2002). Mobile foci of Sp100 do not contain PML: PML bodies are immobile but PML and Sp100 proteins are not. J. Struct. Biol. 140, 180 –188. Yeager, T. R., Neumann, A. A., Englezou, A., Huschtscha, L. I., Noble, J. R., and Reddel, R. R. (1999). Telomerase-negative immortalized human cells contain a novel type of promyelocytic leukemia (PML) body. Cancer Res. 59, 4175– 4179. Zhong, S., Salomoni, P., Ronchetti, S., Guo, A., Ruggero, D., and Pandolﬁ, P. P. (2000). Promyelocytic leukemia protein (PML) and Daxx participate in a novel nuclear pathway for apoptosis. J. Exp. Med. 191, 631– 640.

